; Copy this to a file named $HOME/.sbcl to run POPCO with SBCL.

; Obvious, programmer-friendly default implementation choices aren't 
; prioritized in SBCL ...
(unlock-package 'common-lisp)
; Explanation:
; By default SBCL "locks" the central COMMON-LISP package to prevent
; users from messing with it.  Sounds like a good idea, but apparently
; breaks code that applies type declarations to functions in that
; package.  -Marshall Abrams

; set initial current working dir:
;(setf *DEFAULT-PATHNAME-DEFAULTS* (truename "~/popco"))
; note that a path is a normal, fully-specified path string preceded by "#P".
; truename translates OS abbreviations into this format.
